article.headline: John Square Jr. scores 17 to help Cal State Fullerton edge Idaho State 62-61
article.description: — John Square Jr.'s 17 points helped Cal State Fullerton fend off Idaho State 62-61 on Monday night for the Titans' first victory of the season.

article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- — John Square Jr.'s 17 points helped Cal State Fullerton fend off Idaho State 62-61 on Monday night for the Titans' first victory of the season. Square added five rebounds for the Titans (1-4). Donovan Oday totaled 16 points and seven rebounds. Davis Bynum had 12 points. Jake O'Neil led the Bengals (2-3) with 17 points, 12 rebounds and three steals. Dylan Darling pitched in with 17 points and he hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer to get Idaho State within a point. Isaiah Griffin finished with 16 points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
